It's official! Rustyman is on Twitch and there are a few reasons why I'm making the swap that I will get into more detail below but I'm happy to be on Twitch exclusively going forward 🤘🤘 I've enjoyed my time on Mixer but the in game integration is simply put, better on Twitch, the echocast extension for Borderlands 3 will be launching for consoles soon and I want to be a part of that

Also majorly effecting my decision is my ISP's recent inability to play nice with Mixers FTL tech (mixers big selling point) thus meaning I'm forced to stream with the same delay I'd see on Twitch and removing a major selling point

There are many more reasons I have made this decision... I have not made this call lightly but I'm very excited to see what we can create so let's get going and I hope to see you in my chat in the future 🤙

Here’s some mockups I did for if Euden from Dragalia Lost got into smash! This is one of my personal favorite picks of mine because it’s one of Nintendo’s newest IPs that’s only a mobile game at the moment. Which is why I made mockups for an announcement for a Switch game as well. I feel that Euden has a large set of moves to choose from and plus the dragon aspect will set him apart from the other characters making him very unique. Plus Dragalia Lost is such a great game with an amazing story, great characters with personality and fun game mechanics that deserve a full fledged game on a Nintendo console. Would you like to see Euden in smash or a Dragalia Lost title on the Switch? .

The Lure of the Loot Box for Gamers With Gambling Tendencies 🕹️⠀
.⠀
Gamers who are drawn to “loot boxes”—randomly generated prizes of undisclosed value that can be attained or purchased within a game—bear a closer resemblance to problem gamblers than they do to problem gamers, according to the study published April 16 in Addictive Behaviors.⠀
.⠀
When the researchers analyzed the scores, they found a correlation between excessive engagement with loot boxes and measures of problem gambling, supporting the view that loot boxes are a ‘gamblified’ feature of modern video games. They found a smaller correlation between loot boxes and problem video gaming.⠀
.⠀
📝 https://doi.org/10.1016/j.addbeh.2019.04.009⠀

caption.text: Please Swipe to see all 10 photos. I do these posts DAILY with different hashtags to awaken new minds & to explain long term investing.. So students can understand Stock Splits, Dividend Income (if applicable) & stock market terms.. So these posts are for High School students being brainwashed to learn Shakespeare, Chemistry & Geology instead of “FINANCE & INVESTING".. These posts are for parents that want to teach their children.. Ok.. Lets do the math on Merck (Stock Ticker Symbol is MRK)... Merck was around $30 per share in 1985.. So $15,000 would afford about 500 shares in 1985 ($15,000 / $30 = 500 SHARES).... Since 1985, Merck has done two 2-for-1 stock splits & two 3-for-1 stock split... A 2-for-1 stock split is when a company doubles the number of shares you own and cuts the price of the stock in half... So if you owned 200 shares of COMPANY ABC at $80 per share... After the 2-for-1 stock split you would own 400 shares and the price of the stock would be cut in half from $80 to $40.. Companies do stock splits to keep the price of the stock affordable... So this is how your original 500 shares would have multiplied after the stock splits .... 500 X 2 X 2 X 3 X 3 = 18,000 SHARES OF Merck ... So now in 2019, your original 500 shares of Merck, have multiplied to 18,000 shares because of all the stock splits.. Today Merck is at about $84 a share so your investment today would be worth $1,512,000.00 (18,000 SHARES X $84 PER SHARE). Merck pays a yearly Dividend of $2.20 per share so you would also receive yearly Dividend Income for over $35,000  each year ($2.20 X 18,000 SHARES OWNED)... You would be worth over 3 Million Dollars if you invested $75 per week into shares since 1985 instead of just investing 15K once.. As promised, here's my gaining follows post. Hope this helps you guys out!

1. Have a positive attitude- being positive really draws people in and makes them feel good. If you keep a positive attitude when posting and interacting with others, this will help you out.
2. Post about what you love- posting about things you enjoy is always a good idea and most likely, you'll find others who love those things as well.
3. Encourage and lift others up- when trying to gain followers, always try to give them a feeling of accomplishment. Give them some nice comments and likes as often as you can.
4. Follow people with similar interests- if your Instagram is new, you'll especially need to follow lots of other accounts to help you gain a following, but make sure to stick to instagrams similar to yours so that your audience enjoys what they see.
5. Stay connected- interact with your fans and don't be afraid to promote your other medias, but don't over do it. Keep the promotion on a moderate level.

Hope this helped guys! If you have any questions, comment below!

caption.text:
I've finally finished my quest! 😁 22 Super Mario games completed, played in chronological order with the original software and hardware like Nintendo intended. What a ride!
~
I started this because as a big fan of Mario games there was quite a few I hadn't completed or even played! I also wanted to find out which game out of the whole series was my favourite. Was there a game I hadn't played which would be my new all time favourite? What's my least favourite? How have the games evolved over time? These were the questions I wanted to find out.
~
I've compiled my list, ranking all 22 games from best to worst, based on how much fun I had playing each one. I'll post the list shortly - it'll be interesting to see where your favourite game ranks!

preview_comments.text: So great to see my boy @ixtran make this line up, totally over the moon for him. We started off as cosplayer and photographer and now extremely close friends! Appreciation for all his hard work epic to see 😍😍

caption.text:
MONTHLY REPORT - 5
Here is finally the fifth monthly report. The cosplay archive I would like to create with my page is getting bigger and bigger. The page has passed 200 followers and now has almost reached 300 followers. This month Milan Games Week was held where I met the really nice and talented @atena_cosplay . I took a photo of his beautiful Pizza Delivery Sivir cosplay that I posted in the last few days but I didn't include it among the best cosplay of the month because I think there were better ones than her one even though I really like it very much.
